C++:
g++ -O2 -fopenmp main.cpp

In main.cpp, check that the file path for the input is correct.
This will outout a file named density.txt which contains the new computed values.

Python:

Install Numba first: https://numba.pydata.org/numba-doc/dev/user/installing.html

conda install numba
conda install cudatoolkit

To plot the results, use:

gnuplot -p plot.gnu


Exercise:
1) Add OpenMP directives to enable parallel execution with threads
2) Add OpenMP 4.5 directives to enable GPU offloading

Tip: You only need to modify one line (indicated with comments) before the main loop.
